channel.title: Rsc 204
channel.description:
Has there been any attempt by anyone to crack open Mudclient204 (the current RSC one) and figure out how to use the current .jag files that are apart of it? Does anyone have the current .jag files? I grabbed them off Jagex's servers today to play around with em. Going to attempt to decompile the new client as well.
Thoughts?[br][br][size=1]Posted on: July 02, 2008, 01:39:23 AM[/size][hr]Btw, if you want the files - PM me your MSN and I'll message you with link.

item.title: Rsc 204
item.dc:creator: @vortex vortex
item.description:
@vortex wrote:

As you can see the jag/mem versions have not changed from 202, far as I know only difference between 202 and 204 is that the packet ID’s differ.
http://uppit.com/WBZ0RC - mc deobbed and renamed
http://uppit.com/2ODRR9 - loader

http://classic.runescape.com/client2/mudclient204.jar http://classic.runescape.com/client2/loader204.jar http://classic.runescape.com/client2/config85.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/entity24.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/jagex.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/land63.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/maps63.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/media58.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/models36.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/textures17.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/filter2.jag http://classic.runescape.com/client2/entity24.mem http://classic.runescape.com/client2/land63.mem http://classic.runescape.com/client2/maps63.mem http://classic.runescape.com/client2/sounds1.mem
  • Unless you want to mess up with the chat filter use a refactored 202 imo
